132/* Holds switches parsed by c_common_handle_option (), but whose
133 handling is deferred to c_common_post_options (). */
134static void defer_opt (enum opt_code, const char *);
135static struct deferred_opt
136{
137 enum opt_code code;
138 const char *arg;
139} *deferred_opts;
140
141
142extern const unsigned int
143c_family_lang_mask = (CL_C | CL_CXX | CL_ObjC | CL_ObjCXX);
144
145/* Defer option CODE with argument ARG. */
146static void
147defer_opt (enum opt_code code, const char *arg)
148{
149 deferred_opts[deferred_count].code = code;
150 deferred_opts[deferred_count].arg = arg;
151 deferred_count++;
152}
153
154/* Return language mask for option parsing. */
155unsigned int
156c_common_option_lang_mask (void)
157{
158 static const unsigned int lang_flags[] = {CL_C, CL_ObjC, CL_CXX, CL_ObjCXX};
159
160 return lang_flags[c_language];
161}
162
163/* Diagnostic finalizer for C/C++/Objective-C/Objective-C++. */
164static void
165c_diagnostic_finalizer (diagnostic_context *context,
166 diagnostic_info *diagnostic)
167{
168 diagnostic_show_locus (context, diagnostic->richloc, diagnostic->kind);
169 /* By default print macro expansion contexts in the diagnostic
170 finalizer -- for tokens resulting from macro expansion. */
171 virt_loc_aware_diagnostic_finalizer (context, diagnostic);
172 pp_destroy_prefix (context->printer);
173 pp_flush (context->printer);
174}
175
176/* Common default settings for diagnostics. */
177void
178c_common_diagnostics_set_defaults (diagnostic_context *context)
179{
180 diagnostic_finalizer (context) = c_diagnostic_finalizer;
181 context->opt_permissive = OPT_fpermissive;
182}
183
184/* Whether options from all C-family languages should be accepted
185 quietly. */
186static bool accept_all_c_family_options = false;
187
188/* Return whether to complain about a wrong-language option. */
189bool
190c_common_complain_wrong_lang_p (const struct cl_option *option)
191{
192 if (accept_all_c_family_options
193 && (option->flags & c_family_lang_mask))
194 return false;
195
196 return true;
197}
198
199/* Initialize options structure OPTS. */
200void
201c_common_init_options_struct (struct gcc_options *opts)
202{
203 opts->x_flag_exceptions = c_dialect_cxx ();
204 opts->x_warn_pointer_arith = c_dialect_cxx ();
205 opts->x_warn_write_strings = c_dialect_cxx ();
206 opts->x_flag_warn_unused_result = true;
207
208 /* By default, C99-like requirements for complex multiply and divide. */
209 opts->x_flag_complex_method = 2;
210}
211
212/* Common initialization before calling option handlers. */
213void
214c_common_init_options (unsigned int decoded_options_count,
215 struct cl_decoded_option *decoded_options)
216{
217 unsigned int i;
218 struct cpp_callbacks *cb;
219
220 g_string_concat_db
221 = new (ggc_alloc <string_concat_db> ()) string_concat_db ();
222
223 parse_in = cpp_create_reader (c_dialect_cxx () ? CLK_GNUCXX: CLK_GNUC89,
224 ident_hash, line_table);
225 cb = cpp_get_callbacks (parse_in);
226 cb->error = c_cpp_error;
227
228 cpp_opts = cpp_get_options (parse_in);
229 cpp_opts->dollars_in_ident = DOLLARS_IN_IDENTIFIERS;
230 cpp_opts->objc = c_dialect_objc ();
231
232 /* Reset to avoid warnings on internal definitions. We set it just
233 before passing on command-line options to cpplib. */
234 cpp_opts->warn_dollars = 0;
235
236 deferred_opts = XNEWVEC (struct deferred_opt, decoded_options_count);
237
238 if (c_language == clk_c)
239 {
240 /* The default for C is gnu11. */
241 set_std_c11 (false /* ISO */);
242
243 /* If preprocessing assembly language, accept any of the C-family
244 front end options since the driver may pass them through. */
245 for (i = 1; i < decoded_options_count; i++)
246 if (decoded_options[i].opt_index == OPT_lang_asm)
247 {
248 accept_all_c_family_options = true;
249 break;
250 }
251 }
252
253 /* Set C++ standard to C++14 if not specified on the command line. */
254 if (c_dialect_cxx ())
255 set_std_cxx14 (/*ISO*/false);
256
257 global_dc->colorize_source_p = true;
258}
259
260/* Handle switch SCODE with argument ARG. VALUE is true, unless no-
261 form of an -f or -W option was given. Returns false if the switch was
262 invalid, true if valid. Use HANDLERS in recursive handle_option calls. */
263bool
264c_common_handle_option (size_t scode, const char *arg, int value,
265 int kind, location_t loc,
266 const struct cl_option_handlers *handlers)
267{
268 const struct cl_option *option = &cl_options[scode];
269 enum opt_code code = (enum opt_code) scode;
270 bool result = true;
271
272 /* Prevent resetting the language standard to a C dialect when the driver
273 has already determined that we're looking at assembler input. */
274 bool preprocessing_asm_p = (cpp_get_options (parse_in)->lang == CLK_ASM);
275
276 switch (code)
277 {
278 default:
279 if (cl_options[code].flags & c_family_lang_mask)
280 {
281 if ((option->flags & CL_TARGET)
282 && ! targetcm.handle_c_option (scode, arg, value))
283 result = false;
284 break;
285 }
286 result = false;
287 break;
288
289 case OPT__output_pch_:
290 pch_file = arg;
291 break;
292
293 case OPT_A:
294 defer_opt (code, arg);
295 break;
296
297 case OPT_C:
298 cpp_opts->discard_comments = 0;
299 break;
300
301 case OPT_CC:
302 cpp_opts->discard_comments = 0;
303 cpp_opts->discard_comments_in_macro_exp = 0;
304 break;
305
306 case OPT_cxx_isystem:
307 add_path (xstrdup (arg), SYSTEM, 1, true);
308 break;
309
310 case OPT_D:
311 defer_opt (code, arg);
312 break;
313
314 case OPT_H:
315 cpp_opts->print_include_names = 1;
316 break;
317
318 case OPT_F:
319 TARGET_OPTF (xstrdup (arg));
320 break;
321
322 case OPT_I:
323 if (strcmp (arg, "-"))
324 add_path (xstrdup (arg), BRACKET, 0, true);
325 else
326 {
327 if (quote_chain_split)
328 error ("-I- specified twice");
329 quote_chain_split = true;
330 split_quote_chain ();
331 inform (input_location, "obsolete option -I- used, please use -iquote instead");
332 }
333 break;
334
335 case OPT_M:
336 case OPT_MM:
337 /* When doing dependencies with -M or -MM, suppress normal
338 preprocessed output, but still do -dM etc. as software
339 depends on this. Preprocessed output does occur if -MD, -MMD
340 or environment var dependency generation is used. */
341 cpp_opts->deps.style = (code == OPT_M ? DEPS_SYSTEM: DEPS_USER);
342 flag_no_output = 1;
343 break;
344
345 case OPT_MD:
346 case OPT_MMD:
347 cpp_opts->deps.style = (code == OPT_MD ? DEPS_SYSTEM: DEPS_USER);
348 cpp_opts->deps.need_preprocessor_output = true;
349 deps_file = arg;
350 break;
351
352 case OPT_MF:
353 deps_seen = true;
354 deps_file = arg;
355 break;
356
357 case OPT_MG:
358 deps_seen = true;
359 cpp_opts->deps.missing_files = true;
360 break;
361
362 case OPT_MP:
363 deps_seen = true;
364 cpp_opts->deps.phony_targets = true;
365 break;
366
367 case OPT_MQ:
368 case OPT_MT:
369 deps_seen = true;
370 defer_opt (code, arg);
371 break;
372
373 case OPT_P:
374 flag_no_line_commands = 1;
375 break;
376
377 case OPT_U:
378 defer_opt (code, arg);
379 break;
380
381 case OPT_Wall:
382 /* ??? Don't add new options here. Use LangEnabledBy in c.opt. */
383
384 cpp_opts->warn_num_sign_change = value;
385 break;
386
387 case OPT_Walloca_larger_than_:
388 if (!value)
389 inform (loc, "-Walloca-larger-than=0 is meaningless");
390 break;
391
392 case OPT_Wvla_larger_than_:
393 if (!value)
394 inform (loc, "-Wvla-larger-than=0 is meaningless");
395 break;
396
397 case OPT_Wunknown_pragmas:
398 /* Set to greater than 1, so that even unknown pragmas in
399 system headers will be warned about. */
400 /* ??? There is no way to handle this automatically for now. */
401 warn_unknown_pragmas = value * 2;
402 break;
403
404 case OPT_ansi:
405 if (!c_dialect_cxx ())
406 set_std_c89 (false, true);
407 else
408 set_std_cxx98 (true);
409 break;
410
411 case OPT_d:
412 handle_OPT_d (arg);
413 break;
414
415 case OPT_Wabi_:
416 warn_abi = true;
417 if (value == 1)
418 {
419 warning (0, "%<-Wabi=1%> is not supported, using =2");
420 value = 2;
421 }
422 warn_abi_version = value;
423 if (flag_abi_compat_version == -1)
424 flag_abi_compat_version = value;
425 break;
426
427 case OPT_fcanonical_system_headers:
428 cpp_opts->canonical_system_headers = value;
429 break;
430
431 case OPT_fcond_mismatch:
432 if (!c_dialect_cxx ())
433 {
434 flag_cond_mismatch = value;
435 break;
436 }
437 warning (0, "switch %qs is no longer supported", option->opt_text);
438 break;
439
440 case OPT_fbuiltin_:
441 if (value)
442 result = false;
443 else
444 disable_builtin_function (arg);
445 break;
446
447 case OPT_fdirectives_only:
448 cpp_opts->directives_only = value;
449 break;
450
451 case OPT_fdollars_in_identifiers:
452 cpp_opts->dollars_in_ident = value;
453 break;
454
455 case OPT_ffreestanding:
456 value = !value;
457 /* Fall through. */
458 case OPT_fhosted:
459 flag_hosted = value;
460 flag_no_builtin = !value;
461 break;
462
463 case OPT_fconstant_string_class_:
464 constant_string_class_name = arg;
465 break;
466
467 case OPT_fextended_identifiers:
468 cpp_opts->extended_identifiers = value;
469 break;
470
471 case OPT_foperator_names:
472 cpp_opts->operator_names = value;
473 break;
474
475 case OPT_fpch_deps:
476 cpp_opts->restore_pch_deps = value;
477 break;
478
479 case OPT_fpch_preprocess:
480 flag_pch_preprocess = value;
481 break;
482
483 case OPT_fpermissive:
484 flag_permissive = value;
485 global_dc->permissive = value;
486 break;
487
488 case OPT_fpreprocessed:
489 cpp_opts->preprocessed = value;
490 break;
491
492 case OPT_fdebug_cpp:
493 cpp_opts->debug = 1;
494 break;
495
496 case OPT_ftrack_macro_expansion:
497 if (value)
498 value = 2;
499 /* Fall Through. */
500
501 case OPT_ftrack_macro_expansion_:
502 if (arg && *arg != '\0')
503 cpp_opts->track_macro_expansion = value;
504 else
505 cpp_opts->track_macro_expansion = 2;
506 break;
507
508 case OPT_frepo:
509 flag_use_repository = value;
510 if (value)
511 flag_implicit_templates = 0;
512 break;
513
514 case OPT_ftabstop_:
515 /* It is documented that we silently ignore silly values. */
516 if (value >= 1 && value <= 100)
517 cpp_opts->tabstop = value;
518 break;
519
520 case OPT_fexec_charset_:
521 cpp_opts->narrow_charset = arg;
522 break;
523
524 case OPT_fwide_exec_charset_:
525 cpp_opts->wide_charset = arg;
526 break;
527
528 case OPT_finput_charset_:
529 cpp_opts->input_charset = arg;
530 break;
531
532 case OPT_ftemplate_depth_:
533 max_tinst_depth = value;
534 break;
535
536 case OPT_fvisibility_inlines_hidden:
537 visibility_options.inlines_hidden = value;
538 break;
539
540 case OPT_femit_struct_debug_baseonly:
541 set_struct_debug_option (&global_options, loc, "base");
542 break;
543
544 case OPT_femit_struct_debug_reduced:
545 set_struct_debug_option (&global_options, loc,
546 "dir:ord:sys,dir:gen:any,ind:base");
547 break;
548
549 case OPT_femit_struct_debug_detailed_:
550 set_struct_debug_option (&global_options, loc, arg);
551 break;
552
553 case OPT_fext_numeric_literals:
554 cpp_opts->ext_numeric_literals = value;
555 break;
556
557 case OPT_idirafter:
558 add_path (xstrdup (arg), AFTER, 0, true);
559 break;
560
561 case OPT_imacros:
562 case OPT_include:
563 defer_opt (code, arg);
564 break;
565
566 case OPT_imultilib:
567 imultilib = arg;
568 break;
569
570 case OPT_iprefix:
571 iprefix = arg;
572 break;
573
574 case OPT_iquote:
575 add_path (xstrdup (arg), QUOTE, 0, true);
576 break;
577
578 case OPT_iremap:
579 add_cpp_remap_path (arg);
580 break;
581
582 case OPT_isysroot:
583 sysroot = arg;
584 break;
585
586 case OPT_isystem:
587 add_path (xstrdup (arg), SYSTEM, 0, true);
588 break;
589
590 case OPT_iwithprefix:
591 add_prefixed_path (arg, SYSTEM);
592 break;
593
594 case OPT_iwithprefixbefore:
595 add_prefixed_path (arg, BRACKET);
596 break;
597
598 case OPT_lang_asm:
599 cpp_set_lang (parse_in, CLK_ASM);
600 cpp_opts->dollars_in_ident = false;
601 break;
602
603 case OPT_nostdinc:
604 std_inc = false;
605 break;
606
607 case OPT_nostdinc__:
608 std_cxx_inc = false;
609 break;
610
611 case OPT_o:
612 if (!out_fname)
613 out_fname = arg;
614 else
615 error ("output filename specified twice");
616 break;
617
618 case OPT_print_objc_runtime_info:
619 print_struct_values = 1;
620 break;
621
622 case OPT_remap:
623 cpp_opts->remap = 1;
624 break;
625
626 case OPT_std_c__98:
627 case OPT_std_gnu__98:
628 if (!preprocessing_asm_p)
629 set_std_cxx98 (code == OPT_std_c__98 /* ISO */);
630 break;
631
632 case OPT_std_c__11:
633 case OPT_std_gnu__11:
634 if (!preprocessing_asm_p)
635 set_std_cxx11 (code == OPT_std_c__11 /* ISO */);
636 break;
637
638 case OPT_std_c__14:
639 case OPT_std_gnu__14:
640 if (!preprocessing_asm_p)
641 set_std_cxx14 (code == OPT_std_c__14 /* ISO */);
642 break;
643
644 case OPT_std_c__1z:
645 case OPT_std_gnu__1z:
646 if (!preprocessing_asm_p)
647 set_std_cxx1z (code == OPT_std_c__1z /* ISO */);
648 break;
649
650 case OPT_std_c90:
651 case OPT_std_iso9899_199409:
652 if (!preprocessing_asm_p)
653 set_std_c89 (code == OPT_std_iso9899_199409 /* c94 */, true /* ISO */);
654 break;
655
656 case OPT_std_gnu90:
657 if (!preprocessing_asm_p)
658 set_std_c89 (false /* c94 */, false /* ISO */);
659 break;
660
661 case OPT_std_c99:
662 if (!preprocessing_asm_p)
663 set_std_c99 (true /* ISO */);
664 break;
665
666 case OPT_std_gnu99:
667 if (!preprocessing_asm_p)
668 set_std_c99 (false /* ISO */);
669 break;
670
671 case OPT_std_c11:
672 if (!preprocessing_asm_p)
673 set_std_c11 (true /* ISO */);
674 break;
675
676 case OPT_std_gnu11:
677 if (!preprocessing_asm_p)
678 set_std_c11 (false /* ISO */);
679 break;
680
681 case OPT_trigraphs:
682 cpp_opts->trigraphs = 1;
683 break;
684
685 case OPT_traditional_cpp:
686 cpp_opts->traditional = 1;
687 break;
688
689 case OPT_v:
690 verbose = true;
691 break;
692 }
693
694 switch (c_language)
695 {
696 case clk_c:
697 C_handle_option_auto (&global_options, &global_options_set,
698 scode, arg, value,
699 c_family_lang_mask, kind,
700 loc, handlers, global_dc);
701 break;
702
703 case clk_objc:
704 ObjC_handle_option_auto (&global_options, &global_options_set,
705 scode, arg, value,
706 c_family_lang_mask, kind,
707 loc, handlers, global_dc);
708 break;
709
710 case clk_cxx:
711 CXX_handle_option_auto (&global_options, &global_options_set,
712 scode, arg, value,
713 c_family_lang_mask, kind,
714 loc, handlers, global_dc);
715 break;
716
717 case clk_objcxx:
718 ObjCXX_handle_option_auto (&global_options, &global_options_set,
719 scode, arg, value,
720 c_family_lang_mask, kind,
721 loc, handlers, global_dc);
722 break;
723
724 default:
725 gcc_unreachable ();
726 }
727
728 cpp_handle_option_auto (&global_options, scode, cpp_opts);
729 return result;
730}

735default_handle_c_option (size_t code ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED,
736 const char *arg ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED,
737 int value ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED)
738{
739 return false;

741
742/* Post-switch processing. */
743bool
744c_common_post_options (const char **pfilename)
745{
746 struct cpp_callbacks *cb;
747
748 /* Canonicalize the input and output filenames. */
749 if (in_fnames == NULL)
750 {
751 in_fnames = XNEWVEC (const char *, 1);
752 in_fnames[0] = "";
753 }
754 else if (strcmp (in_fnames[0], "-") == 0)
755 {
756 if (pch_file)
757 error ("cannot use %<-%> as input filename for a precompiled header");
758
759 in_fnames[0] = "";
760 }
761
762 if (out_fname == NULL || !strcmp (out_fname, "-"))
763 out_fname = "";
764
765 if (cpp_opts->deps.style == DEPS_NONE)
766 check_deps_environment_vars ();
767
768 handle_deferred_opts ();
769
770 sanitize_cpp_opts ();
771
772 register_include_chains (parse_in, sysroot, iprefix, imultilib,
773 std_inc, std_cxx_inc && c_dialect_cxx (), verbose);
774
775#ifdef C_COMMON_OVERRIDE_OPTIONS
776 /* Some machines may reject certain combinations of C
777 language-specific options. */
778 C_COMMON_OVERRIDE_OPTIONS;
779#endif
780
781 /* Excess precision other than "fast" requires front-end
782 support. */
783 if (c_dialect_cxx ())
784 {
785 if (flag_excess_precision_cmdline == EXCESS_PRECISION_STANDARD)
786 sorry ("-fexcess-precision=standard for C++");
787 flag_excess_precision_cmdline = EXCESS_PRECISION_FAST;
788 }
789 else if (flag_excess_precision_cmdline == EXCESS_PRECISION_DEFAULT)
790 flag_excess_precision_cmdline = (flag_iso
791 ? EXCESS_PRECISION_STANDARD
792 : EXCESS_PRECISION_FAST);
793
794 /* ISO C restricts floating-point expression contraction to within
795 source-language expressions (-ffp-contract=on, currently an alias
796 for -ffp-contract=off). */
797 if (flag_iso
798 && !c_dialect_cxx ()
799 && (global_options_set.x_flag_fp_contract_mode
800 == (enum fp_contract_mode) 0)
801 && flag_unsafe_math_optimizations == 0)
802 flag_fp_contract_mode = FP_CONTRACT_OFF;
803
804 /* If we are compiling C, and we are outside of a standards mode,
805 we can permit the new values from ISO/IEC TS 18661-3 for
806 FLT_EVAL_METHOD. Otherwise, we must restrict the possible values to
807 the set specified in ISO C99/C11. */
808 if (!flag_iso
809 && !c_dialect_cxx ()
810 && (global_options_set.x_flag_permitted_flt_eval_methods
811 == PERMITTED_FLT_EVAL_METHODS_DEFAULT))
812 flag_permitted_flt_eval_methods = PERMITTED_FLT_EVAL_METHODS_TS_18661;
813 else
814 flag_permitted_flt_eval_methods = PERMITTED_FLT_EVAL_METHODS_C11;
815
816 /* By default we use C99 inline semantics in GNU99 or C99 mode. C99
817 inline semantics are not supported in GNU89 or C89 mode. */
818 if (flag_gnu89_inline == -1)
819 flag_gnu89_inline = !flag_isoc99;
820 else if (!flag_gnu89_inline && !flag_isoc99)
821 error ("-fno-gnu89-inline is only supported in GNU99 or C99 mode");
822
823 /* Default to ObjC sjlj exception handling if NeXT runtime. */
824 if (flag_objc_sjlj_exceptions < 0)
825 flag_objc_sjlj_exceptions = flag_next_runtime;
826 if (flag_objc_exceptions && !flag_objc_sjlj_exceptions)
827 flag_exceptions = 1;
828
829 /* If -ffreestanding, -fno-hosted or -fno-builtin then disable
830 pattern recognition. */
831 if (!global_options_set.x_flag_tree_loop_distribute_patterns
832 && flag_no_builtin)
833 flag_tree_loop_distribute_patterns = 0;
834
835 /* -Woverlength-strings is off by default, but is enabled by -Wpedantic.
836 It is never enabled in C++, as the minimum limit is not normative
837 in that standard. */
838 if (c_dialect_cxx ())
839 warn_overlength_strings = 0;
840
841 /* Wmain is enabled by default in C++ but not in C. */
842 /* Wmain is disabled by default for -ffreestanding (!flag_hosted),
843 even if -Wall or -Wpedantic was given (warn_main will be 2 if set
844 by -Wall, 1 if set by -Wmain). */
845 if (warn_main == -1)
846 warn_main = (c_dialect_cxx () && flag_hosted) ? 1 : 0;
847 else if (warn_main == 2)
848 warn_main = flag_hosted ? 1 : 0;
849
850 /* In C, -Wall and -Wc++-compat enable -Wenum-compare; if it has not
851 yet been set, it is disabled by default. In C++, it is enabled
852 by default. */
853 if (warn_enum_compare == -1)
854 warn_enum_compare = c_dialect_cxx () ? 1 : 0;
855
856 /* -Wpacked-bitfield-compat is on by default for the C languages. The
857 warning is issued in stor-layout.c which is not part of the front-end so
858 we need to selectively turn it on here. */
859 if (warn_packed_bitfield_compat == -1)
860 warn_packed_bitfield_compat = 1;
861
862 /* Special format checking options don't work without -Wformat; warn if
863 they are used. */
864 if (!warn_format)
865 {
866 warning (OPT_Wformat_y2k,
867 "-Wformat-y2k ignored without -Wformat");
868 warning (OPT_Wformat_extra_args,
869 "-Wformat-extra-args ignored without -Wformat");
870 warning (OPT_Wformat_zero_length,
871 "-Wformat-zero-length ignored without -Wformat");
872 warning (OPT_Wformat_nonliteral,
873 "-Wformat-nonliteral ignored without -Wformat");
874 warning (OPT_Wformat_contains_nul,
875 "-Wformat-contains-nul ignored without -Wformat");
876 warning (OPT_Wformat_security,
877 "-Wformat-security ignored without -Wformat");
878 }
879
880 /* -Wimplicit-function-declaration is enabled by default for C99. */
881 if (warn_implicit_function_declaration == -1)
882 warn_implicit_function_declaration = flag_isoc99;
883
884 /* -Wimplicit-int is enabled by default for C99. */
885 if (warn_implicit_int == -1)
886 warn_implicit_int = flag_isoc99;
887
888 /* -Wshift-overflow is enabled by default in C99 and C++11 modes. */
889 if (warn_shift_overflow == -1)
890 warn_shift_overflow = cxx_dialect >= cxx11 || flag_isoc99;
891
892 /* -Wshift-negative-value is enabled by -Wextra in C99 and C++11 modes. */
893 if (warn_shift_negative_value == -1)
894 warn_shift_negative_value = (extra_warnings
895 && (cxx_dialect >= cxx11 || flag_isoc99));
896
897 /* -Wregister is enabled by default in C++17. */
898 if (!global_options_set.x_warn_register)
899 warn_register = cxx_dialect >= cxx1z;
900
901 /* Declone C++ 'structors if -Os. */
902 if (flag_declone_ctor_dtor == -1)
903 flag_declone_ctor_dtor = optimize_size;
904
905 if (warn_abi_version == -1)
906 {
907 if (flag_abi_compat_version != -1)
908 warn_abi_version = flag_abi_compat_version;
909 else
910 warn_abi_version = 0;
911 }
912
913 if (flag_abi_compat_version == 1)
914 {
915 warning (0, "%<-fabi-compat-version=1%> is not supported, using =2");
916 flag_abi_compat_version = 2;
917 }
918 else if (flag_abi_compat_version == -1)
919 {
920 /* Generate compatibility aliases for ABI v10 (6.1) by default. */
921 flag_abi_compat_version
922 = (flag_abi_version == 0 ? 10 : 0);
923 }
924
925 /* Change flag_abi_version to be the actual current ABI level for the
926 benefit of c_cpp_builtins. */
927 if (flag_abi_version == 0)
928 flag_abi_version = 11;
929
930 /* By default, enable the new inheriting constructor semantics along with ABI
931 11. New and old should coexist fine, but it is a change in what
932 artificial symbols are generated. */
933 if (!global_options_set.x_flag_new_inheriting_ctors)
934 flag_new_inheriting_ctors = abi_version_at_least (11);
935
936 /* For GCC 7, only enable DR150 resolution by default if -std=c++1z. */
937 if (!global_options_set.x_flag_new_ttp)
938 flag_new_ttp = (cxx_dialect >= cxx1z);
939
940 if (cxx_dialect >= cxx11)
941 {
942 /* If we're allowing C++0x constructs, don't warn about C++98
943 identifiers which are keywords in C++0x. */
944 warn_cxx11_compat = 0;
945 cpp_opts->cpp_warn_cxx11_compat = 0;
946
947 if (warn_narrowing == -1)
948 warn_narrowing = 1;
949
950 /* Unless -f{,no-}ext-numeric-literals has been used explicitly,
951 for -std=c++{11,14,1z} default to -fno-ext-numeric-literals. */
952 if (flag_iso && !global_options_set.x_flag_ext_numeric_literals)
953 cpp_opts->ext_numeric_literals = 0;
954 }
955 else if (warn_narrowing == -1)
956 warn_narrowing = 0;
957
958 /* C++17 has stricter evaluation order requirements; let's use some of them
959 for earlier C++ as well, so chaining works as expected. */
960 if (c_dialect_cxx ()
961 && flag_strong_eval_order == -1)
962 flag_strong_eval_order = (cxx_dialect >= cxx1z ? 2 : 1);
963
964 /* Global sized deallocation is new in C++14. */
965 if (flag_sized_deallocation == -1)
966 flag_sized_deallocation = (cxx_dialect >= cxx14);
967
968 if (flag_extern_tls_init)
969 {
970#if !defined (ASM_OUTPUT_DEF) || !SUPPORTS_WEAK
971 /* Lazy TLS initialization for a variable in another TU requires
972 alias and weak reference support. */
973 if (flag_extern_tls_init > 0)
974 sorry ("external TLS initialization functions not supported "
975 "on this target");
976 flag_extern_tls_init = 0;
977#else
978 flag_extern_tls_init = 1;
979#endif
980 }
981
982 if (flag_preprocess_only)
983 {
984 /* Open the output now. We must do so even if flag_no_output is
985 on, because there may be other output than from the actual
986 preprocessing (e.g. from -dM). */
987 if (out_fname[0] == '\0')
988 out_stream = stdout;
989 else
990 out_stream = fopen (out_fname, "w");
991
992 if (out_stream == NULL)
993 {
994 fatal_error (input_location, "opening output file %s: %m", out_fname);
995 return false;
996 }
997
998 if (num_in_fnames > 1)
999 error ("too many filenames given. Type %s --help for usage",
1000 progname);
1001
1002 init_pp_output (out_stream);
1003 }
1004 else
1005 {
1006 init_c_lex ();
1007
1008 /* When writing a PCH file, avoid reading some other PCH file,
1009 because the default address space slot then can't be used
1010 for the output PCH file. */
1011 if (pch_file)
1012 {
1013 c_common_no_more_pch ();
1014 /* Only -g0 and -gdwarf* are supported with PCH, for other
1015 debug formats we warn here and refuse to load any PCH files. */
1016 if (write_symbols != NO_DEBUG && write_symbols != DWARF2_DEBUG)
1017 warning (OPT_Wdeprecated,
1018 "the \"%s\" debug format cannot be used with "
1019 "pre-compiled headers", debug_type_names[write_symbols]);
1020 }
1021 else if (write_symbols != NO_DEBUG && write_symbols != DWARF2_DEBUG)
1022 c_common_no_more_pch ();
1023
1024 /* Yuk. WTF is this? I do know ObjC relies on it somewhere. */
1025 input_location = UNKNOWN_LOCATION;
1026 }
1027
1028 cb = cpp_get_callbacks (parse_in);
1029 cb->file_change = cb_file_change;
1030 cb->dir_change = cb_dir_change;
1031 cpp_post_options (parse_in);
1032 init_global_opts_from_cpp (&global_options, cpp_get_options (parse_in));
1033
1034 input_location = UNKNOWN_LOCATION;
1035
1036 *pfilename = this_input_filename
1037 = cpp_read_main_file (parse_in, in_fnames[0]);
1038 /* Don't do any compilation or preprocessing if there is no input file. */
1039 if (this_input_filename == NULL)
1040 {
1041 errorcount++;
1042 return false;
1043 }
1044
1045 if (flag_working_directory
1046 && flag_preprocess_only && !flag_no_line_commands)
1047 pp_dir_change (parse_in, get_src_pwd ());
1048
1049 /* Disable LTO output when outputting a precompiled header. */
1050 if (pch_file && flag_lto)
1051 {
1052 flag_lto = 0;
1053 flag_generate_lto = 0;
1054 }
1055
1056 return flag_preprocess_only;
1057}
1058
1059/* Front end initialization common to C, ObjC and C++. */
1060bool
1061c_common_init (void)
1062{
1063 /* Set up preprocessor arithmetic. Must be done after call to
1064 c_common_nodes_and_builtins for type nodes to be good. */
1065 cpp_opts->precision = TYPE_PRECISION (intmax_type_node);
1066 cpp_opts->char_precision = TYPE_PRECISION (char_type_node);
1067 cpp_opts->int_precision = TYPE_PRECISION (integer_type_node);
1068 cpp_opts->wchar_precision = TYPE_PRECISION (wchar_type_node);
1069 cpp_opts->unsigned_wchar = TYPE_UNSIGNED (wchar_type_node);
1070 cpp_opts->bytes_big_endian = BYTES_BIG_ENDIAN;
1071
1072 /* This can't happen until after wchar_precision and bytes_big_endian
1073 are known. */
1074 cpp_init_iconv (parse_in);
1075
1076 if (version_flag)
1077 {
1078 int i;
1079 fputs ("Compiler executable checksum: ", stderr);
1080 for (i = 0; i < 16; i++)
1081 fprintf (stderr, "%02x", executable_checksum[i]);
1082 putc ('\n', stderr);
1083 }
1084
1085 /* Has to wait until now so that cpplib has its hash table. */
1086 init_pragma ();
1087
1088 if (flag_preprocess_only)
1089 {
1090 c_finish_options ();
1091 preprocess_file (parse_in);
1092 return false;
1093 }
1094
1095 return true;
1096}
1097
1098/* Initialize the integrated preprocessor after debug output has been
1099 initialized; loop over each input file. */
1100void
1101c_common_parse_file (void)
1102{
1103 unsigned int i;
1104
1105 i = 0;
1106 for (;;)
1107 {
1108 c_finish_options ();
1109 /* Open the dump files to use for the original and class dump output
1110 here, to be used during parsing for the current file. */
1111 original_dump_file = dump_begin (TDI_original, &original_dump_flags);
1112 class_dump_file = dump_begin (TDI_class, &class_dump_flags);
1113 pch_init ();
1114 push_file_scope ();
1115 c_parse_file ();
1116 pop_file_scope ();
1117 /* And end the main input file, if the debug writer wants it */
1118 if (debug_hooks->start_end_main_source_file)
1119 (*debug_hooks->end_source_file) (0);
1120 if (++i >= num_in_fnames)
1121 break;
1122 cpp_undef_all (parse_in);
1123 cpp_clear_file_cache (parse_in);
1124 this_input_filename
1125 = cpp_read_main_file (parse_in, in_fnames[i]);
1126 if (original_dump_file)
1127 {
1128 dump_end (TDI_original, original_dump_file);
1129 original_dump_file = NULL;
1130 }
1131 if (class_dump_file)
1132 {
1133 dump_end (TDI_class, class_dump_file);
1134 class_dump_file = NULL;
1135 }
1136 /* If an input file is missing, abandon further compilation.
1137 cpplib has issued a diagnostic. */
1138 if (!this_input_filename)
1139 break;
1140 }
1141
1142 c_parse_final_cleanups ();
1143}
1144
1145/* Returns the appropriate dump file for PHASE to dump with FLAGS. */
1146FILE *
1147get_dump_info (int phase, int *flags)
1148{
1149 gcc_assert (phase == TDI_original || phase == TDI_class);
1150 if (phase == TDI_original)
1151 {
1152 *flags = original_dump_flags;
1153 return original_dump_file;
1154 }
1155 else
1156 {
1157 *flags = class_dump_flags;
1158 return class_dump_file;
1159 }
1160}
1161
1162/* Common finish hook for the C, ObjC and C++ front ends. */
1163void
1164c_common_finish (void)
1165{
1166 FILE *deps_stream = NULL;
1167
1168 /* Don't write the deps file if there are errors. */
1169 if (cpp_opts->deps.style != DEPS_NONE && !seen_error ())
1170 {
1171 /* If -M or -MM was seen without -MF, default output to the
1172 output stream. */
1173 if (!deps_file)
1174 deps_stream = out_stream;
1175 else
1176 {
1177 deps_stream = fopen (deps_file, deps_append ? "a": "w");
1178 if (!deps_stream)
1179 fatal_error (input_location, "opening dependency file %s: %m",
1180 deps_file);
1181 }
1182 }
1183
1184 /* For performance, avoid tearing down cpplib's internal structures
1185 with cpp_destroy (). */
1186 cpp_finish (parse_in, deps_stream);
1187
1188 if (deps_stream && deps_stream != out_stream
1189 && (ferror (deps_stream) || fclose (deps_stream)))
1190 fatal_error (input_location, "closing dependency file %s: %m", deps_file);
1191
1192 if (out_stream && (ferror (out_stream) || fclose (out_stream)))
1193 fatal_error (input_location, "when writing output to %s: %m", out_fname);
1194}
1195
1196/* Either of two environment variables can specify output of
1197 dependencies. Their value is either "OUTPUT_FILE" or "OUTPUT_FILE
1198 DEPS_TARGET", where OUTPUT_FILE is the file to write deps info to
1199 and DEPS_TARGET is the target to mention in the deps. They also
1200 result in dependency information being appended to the output file
1201 rather than overwriting it, and like Sun's compiler
1202 SUNPRO_DEPENDENCIES suppresses the dependency on the main file. */
1203static void
1204check_deps_environment_vars (void)
1205{
1206 char *spec;
1207
1208 spec = getenv ("DEPENDENCIES_OUTPUT");
1209 if (spec)
1210 cpp_opts->deps.style = DEPS_USER;
1211 else
1212 {
1213 spec = getenv ("SUNPRO_DEPENDENCIES");
1214 if (spec)
1215 {
1216 cpp_opts->deps.style = DEPS_SYSTEM;
1217 cpp_opts->deps.ignore_main_file = true;
1218 }
1219 }
1220
1221 if (spec)
1222 {
1223 /* Find the space before the DEPS_TARGET, if there is one. */
1224 char *s = strchr (spec, ' ');
1225 if (s)
1226 {
1227 /* Let the caller perform MAKE quoting. */
1228 defer_opt (OPT_MT, s + 1);
1229 *s = '\0';
1230 }
1231
1232 /* Command line -MF overrides environment variables and default. */
1233 if (!deps_file)
1234 deps_file = spec;
1235
1236 deps_append = 1;
1237 deps_seen = true;
1238 }
1239}
1240
1241/* Handle deferred command line switches. */
1242static void
1243handle_deferred_opts (void)
1244{
1245 size_t i;
1246 struct deps *deps;
1247
1248 /* Avoid allocating the deps buffer if we don't need it.
1249 (This flag may be true without there having been -MT or -MQ
1250 options, but we'll still need the deps buffer.) */
1251 if (!deps_seen)
1252 return;
1253
1254 deps = cpp_get_deps (parse_in);
1255
1256 for (i = 0; i < deferred_count; i++)
1257 {
1258 struct deferred_opt *opt = &deferred_opts[i];
1259
1260 if (opt->code == OPT_MT || opt->code == OPT_MQ)
1261 deps_add_target (deps, opt->arg, opt->code == OPT_MQ);
1262 }
1263}
1264
1265/* These settings are appropriate for GCC, but not necessarily so for
1266 cpplib as a library. */
1267static void
1268sanitize_cpp_opts (void)
1269{
1270 /* If we don't know what style of dependencies to output, complain
1271 if any other dependency switches have been given. */
1272 if (deps_seen && cpp_opts->deps.style == DEPS_NONE)
1273 error ("to generate dependencies you must specify either -M or -MM");
1274
1275 /* -dM and dependencies suppress normal output; do it here so that
1276 the last -d[MDN] switch overrides earlier ones. */
1277 if (flag_dump_macros == 'M')
1278 flag_no_output = 1;
1279
1280 /* By default, -fdirectives-only implies -dD. This allows subsequent phases
1281 to perform proper macro expansion. */
1282 if (cpp_opts->directives_only && !cpp_opts->preprocessed && !flag_dump_macros)
1283 flag_dump_macros = 'D';
1284
1285 /* Disable -dD, -dN and -dI if normal output is suppressed. Allow
1286 -dM since at least glibc relies on -M -dM to work. */
1287 /* Also, flag_no_output implies flag_no_line_commands, always. */
1288 if (flag_no_output)
1289 {
1290 if (flag_dump_macros != 'M')
1291 flag_dump_macros = 0;
1292 flag_dump_includes = 0;
1293 flag_no_line_commands = 1;
1294 }
1295 else if (cpp_opts->deps.missing_files)
1296 error ("-MG may only be used with -M or -MM");
1297
1298 cpp_opts->unsigned_char = !flag_signed_char;
1299 cpp_opts->stdc_0_in_system_headers = STDC_0_IN_SYSTEM_HEADERS;
1300
1301 /* Wlong-long is disabled by default. It is enabled by:
1302 [-Wpedantic | -Wtraditional] -std=[gnu|c]++98 ; or
1303 [-Wpedantic | -Wtraditional] -std=non-c99
1304
1305 Either -Wlong-long or -Wno-long-long override any other settings.
1306 ??? These conditions should be handled in c.opt. */
1307 if (warn_long_long == -1)
1308 {
1309 warn_long_long = ((pedantic || warn_traditional)
1310 && (c_dialect_cxx () ? cxx_dialect == cxx98 : !flag_isoc99));
1311 cpp_opts->cpp_warn_long_long = warn_long_long;
1312 }
1313
1314 /* If we're generating preprocessor output, emit current directory
1315 if explicitly requested or if debugging information is enabled.
1316 ??? Maybe we should only do it for debugging formats that
1317 actually output the current directory? */
1318 if (flag_working_directory == -1)
1319 flag_working_directory = (debug_info_level != DINFO_LEVEL_NONE);
1320
1321 if (warn_implicit_fallthrough < 5)
1322 cpp_opts->cpp_warn_implicit_fallthrough = warn_implicit_fallthrough;
1323 else
1324 cpp_opts->cpp_warn_implicit_fallthrough = 0;
1325
1326 if (cpp_opts->directives_only)
1327 {
1328 if (cpp_warn_unused_macros)
1329 error ("-fdirectives-only is incompatible with -Wunused_macros");
1330 if (cpp_opts->traditional)
1331 error ("-fdirectives-only is incompatible with -traditional");
1332 }
1333}
1334
1335/* Add include path with a prefix at the front of its name. */
1336static void
1337add_prefixed_path (const char *suffix, size_t chain)
1338{
1339 char *path;
1340 const char *prefix;
1341 size_t prefix_len, suffix_len;
1342
1343 suffix_len = strlen (suffix);
1344 prefix = iprefix ? iprefix : cpp_GCC_INCLUDE_DIR;
1345 prefix_len = iprefix ? strlen (iprefix) : cpp_GCC_INCLUDE_DIR_len;
1346
1347 path = (char *) xmalloc (prefix_len + suffix_len + 1);
1348 memcpy (path, prefix, prefix_len);
1349 memcpy (path + prefix_len, suffix, suffix_len);
1350 path[prefix_len + suffix_len] = '\0';
1351
1352 add_path (path, chain, 0, false);
1353}
1354
1355/* Handle -D, -U, -A, -imacros, and the first -include. */
1356static void
1357c_finish_options (void)
1358{
1359 if (!cpp_opts->preprocessed)
1360 {
1361 size_t i;
1362
1363 cb_file_change (parse_in,
1364 linemap_check_ordinary (linemap_add (line_table,
1365 LC_RENAME, 0,
1366 _("<built-in>"),
1367 0)));
1368 /* Make sure all of the builtins about to be declared have
1369 BUILTINS_LOCATION has their source_location. */
1370 source_location builtins_loc = BUILTINS_LOCATION;
1371 cpp_force_token_locations (parse_in, &builtins_loc);
1372
1373 cpp_init_builtins (parse_in, flag_hosted);
1374 c_cpp_builtins (parse_in);
1375
1376 cpp_stop_forcing_token_locations (parse_in);
1377
1378 /* We're about to send user input to cpplib, so make it warn for
1379 things that we previously (when we sent it internal definitions)
1380 told it to not warn.
1381
1382 C99 permits implementation-defined characters in identifiers.
1383 The documented meaning of -std= is to turn off extensions that
1384 conflict with the specified standard, and since a strictly
1385 conforming program cannot contain a '$', we do not condition
1386 their acceptance on the -std= setting. */
1387 cpp_opts->warn_dollars = (cpp_opts->cpp_pedantic && !cpp_opts->c99);
1388
1389 cb_file_change (parse_in,
1390 linemap_check_ordinary (linemap_add (line_table, LC_RENAME, 0,
1391 _("<command-line>"), 0)));
1392
1393 for (i = 0; i < deferred_count; i++)
1394 {
1395 struct deferred_opt *opt = &deferred_opts[i];
1396
1397 if (opt->code == OPT_D)
1398 cpp_define (parse_in, opt->arg);
1399 else if (opt->code == OPT_U)
1400 cpp_undef (parse_in, opt->arg);
1401 else if (opt->code == OPT_A)
1402 {
1403 if (opt->arg[0] == '-')
1404 cpp_unassert (parse_in, opt->arg + 1);
1405 else
1406 cpp_assert (parse_in, opt->arg);
1407 }
1408 }
1409
1410 /* Start the main input file, if the debug writer wants it. */
1411 if (debug_hooks->start_end_main_source_file
1412 && !flag_preprocess_only)
1413 (*debug_hooks->start_source_file) (0, this_input_filename);
1414
1415 /* Handle -imacros after -D and -U. */
1416 for (i = 0; i < deferred_count; i++)
1417 {
1418 struct deferred_opt *opt = &deferred_opts[i];
1419
1420 if (opt->code == OPT_imacros
1421 && cpp_push_include (parse_in, opt->arg))
1422 {
1423 /* Disable push_command_line_include callback for now. */
1424 include_cursor = deferred_count + 1;
1425 cpp_scan_nooutput (parse_in);
1426 }
1427 }
1428 }
1429 else
1430 {
1431 if (cpp_opts->directives_only)
1432 cpp_init_special_builtins (parse_in);
1433
1434 /* Start the main input file, if the debug writer wants it. */
1435 if (debug_hooks->start_end_main_source_file
1436 && !flag_preprocess_only)
1437 (*debug_hooks->start_source_file) (0, this_input_filename);
1438 }
1439
1440 include_cursor = 0;
1441 push_command_line_include ();
1442}
1443
1444/* Give CPP the next file given by -include, if any. */
1445static void
1446push_command_line_include (void)
1447{
1448 /* This can happen if disabled by -imacros for example.
1449 Punt so that we don't set "<command-line>" as the filename for
1450 the header. */
1451 if (include_cursor > deferred_count)
1452 return;
1453
1454 if (!done_preinclude)
1455 {
1456 done_preinclude = true;
1457 if (flag_hosted && std_inc && !cpp_opts->preprocessed)
1458 {
1459 const char *preinc = targetcm.c_preinclude ();
1460 if (preinc && cpp_push_default_include (parse_in, preinc))
1461 return;
1462 }
1463 }
1464
1465 pch_cpp_save_state ();
1466
1467 while (include_cursor < deferred_count)
1468 {
1469 struct deferred_opt *opt = &deferred_opts[include_cursor++];
1470
1471 if (!cpp_opts->preprocessed && opt->code == OPT_include
1472 && cpp_push_include (parse_in, opt->arg))
1473 return;
1474 }
1475
1476 if (include_cursor == deferred_count)
1477 {
1478 include_cursor++;
1479 /* -Wunused-macros should only warn about macros defined hereafter. */
1480 cpp_opts->warn_unused_macros = cpp_warn_unused_macros;
1481 /* Restore the line map from <command line>. */
1482 if (!cpp_opts->preprocessed)
1483 cpp_change_file (parse_in, LC_RENAME, this_input_filename);
1484
1485 /* Set this here so the client can change the option if it wishes,
1486 and after stacking the main file so we don't trace the main file. */
1487 line_table->trace_includes = cpp_opts->print_include_names;
1488 }
1489}
1490
1491/* File change callback. Has to handle -include files. */
1492static void
1493cb_file_change (cpp_reader * ARG_UNUSED (pfile),
1494 const line_map_ordinary *new_map)
1495{
1496 if (flag_preprocess_only)
1497 pp_file_change (new_map);
1498 else
1499 fe_file_change (new_map);
1500
1501 if (new_map
1502 && (new_map->reason == LC_ENTER || new_map->reason == LC_RENAME))
1503 {
1504 /* Signal to plugins that a file is included. This could happen
1505 several times with the same file path, e.g. because of
1506 several '#include' or '#line' directives... */
1507 invoke_plugin_callbacks
1508 (PLUGIN_INCLUDE_FILE,
1509 const_cast<char*> (ORDINARY_MAP_FILE_NAME (new_map)));
1510 }
1511
1512 if (new_map == 0 || (new_map->reason == LC_LEAVE && MAIN_FILE_P (new_map)))
1513 {
1514 pch_cpp_save_state ();
1515 push_command_line_include ();
1516 }
1517}
1518
1519void
1520cb_dir_change (cpp_reader * ARG_UNUSED (pfile), const char *dir)
1521{
1522 if (!set_src_pwd (dir))
1523 warning (0, "too late for # directive to set debug directory");
1524}

1526/* Set the C 89 standard (with 1994 amendments if C94, without GNU
1527 extensions if ISO). There is no concept of gnu94. */
1528static void
1529set_std_c89 (int c94, int iso)
1530{
1531 cpp_set_lang (parse_in, c94 ? CLK_STDC94: iso ? CLK_STDC89: CLK_GNUC89);
1532 flag_iso = iso;
1533 flag_no_asm = iso;
1534 flag_no_gnu_keywords = iso;
1535 flag_no_nonansi_builtin = iso;
1536 flag_isoc94 = c94;
1537 flag_isoc99 = 0;
1538 flag_isoc11 = 0;
1539 lang_hooks.name = "GNU C89";
1540}

1630/* Args to -d specify what to dump. Silently ignore
1631 unrecognized options; they may be aimed at toplev.c. */
1632static void
1633handle_OPT_d (const char *arg)
1634{
1635 char c;
1636
1637 while ((c = *arg++) != '\0')
1638 switch (c)
1639 {
1640 case 'M': /* Dump macros only. */
1641 case 'N': /* Dump names. */
1642 case 'D': /* Dump definitions. */
1643 case 'U': /* Dump used macros. */
1644 flag_dump_macros = c;
1645 break;
1646
1647 case 'I':
1648 flag_dump_includes = 1;
1649 break;
1650 }
1651}
